<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/27(Sun.) Ukraine’s resistance offers a useful lesson to Taiwan/ Rise in Global Inflation Widespread and...(Host:Joyce)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=602&amp;p=625#p625"><![CDATA[
3/27(Sun.) Ukraine’s resistance offers a useful lesson to Taiwan/ Rise in Global Inflation Widespread and Persistent (Host: Joyce)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:35 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:35-9:00 pm Debate<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Article 1: Ukraine’s resistance offers a useful lesson to Taiwan<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/2022-03-20/ukraines-resistance-offers-a-useful-lesson-to-taiwan">https://www.latimes.com/politics/story/ ... -to-taiwan</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.Do you think Ukraine’s resistance offers useful lessons to Taiwan?<br /><br />2.China continues to threaten Taiwan. Do you think Ukrainian war may have reduced the chances of an invasion from China?<br /><br />3.The success of Ukraine’s army of reservists and trained civilians is giving Taiwan a model of how to defend ourselves. How could Taiwan do something like that in the event of an invasion?<br /><br />4.Do you think Taiwan’s compulsory training period need to be extended? What’s your opinion about all eligible Taiwanese women need to be included in non-combat training programs, particularly military logistics?<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Article 2: Rise in Global Inflation Widespread and Persistent<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.fitchratings.com/research/sovereigns/rise-in-global-inflation-widespread-persistent-28-02-2022">https://www.fitchratings.com/research/s ... 28-02-2022</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.The Covid19 and Ukraine crisis have wide implications for global business activity. Do you think that could cause severe inflation in Taiwan?<br /><br />2.How to respond when the price of most products have been raised in the face of inflationary cost rises?<br /><br />3.Shipping delays have continued to worsen and freight costs remain hugely elevated. What products are running short on? <br /><br />4.Are you worried that there will be a food crisis? Do you think how large it will be?<br /><br />5.If you see purchase limits on products, will you buy unusually large amounts of a product in anticipation of a large price increase or shortage?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Wed Mar 23, 2022 10:09 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
